an world is your own memories or even the product of your own mind. It just means that it is techno logically supplied to a brain - + now I recall that dream I had in which I ventured into a sensory - deprivation state, either got fed a seeming world or autogenerated it by my very act of perceiving it (viz: the harder I scrutinized it the more real + articulated it became) but had deliberately set up \"an uncanny one t way intrusion from outside\" to remind me: 15 minute clock-timed taped statements which t would hear, i.e. the AI voice. Not only would the contents of its messages remind me, but the very fact of the voice per se would remind me, since (as Lem says) \"they - it - would not belong\" in a sense this whole exegesis which is an attempt to explain 2-3-74 + such things as the AI voice - is working at cross purposes to the device for anamnesis that A197 the AI voice is; this is act one elaborate rationalizing pseudo-explanation to create a system in which e.g. the AI voice not \"an uncanny one - way intrusion is from outside, amounting to a technological foul-up by which the truth - the true state sleep is revealed\"! This exegesis is ratiocination serving to keep the illusion intact, whereas I should be trying to \"wake up,\" as it were - here \"anamnesis\" equals waking up, in which case the meta-abstraction is pure + simply a waking up (+ therefore is an insight (within a group of insights. not but is the insight, there only being one, + that one is that if the past is coaxially here, then \"here\" + \"now\" are illusory, spation temporality is illusory, world is illusory: the Golden Fish sign did not belong but was \"an uncanny one-way intrusion from outside revealing that \"world\" is spurious + what occurs to me at once, now, is: + the real world is here as a book, the Bible I know how this works because. I used + novel The idea in \"TMITHC,\" H. Abendson's which is not exactly a book but a world this corrolates converted into information. with my reading of Luke that night when t was loaded, + with the scriptural material in \"Tears.\" as in \"Finnegans wake\" the Acts material in \"Tears\" is the real world intruding on the dreamer + the dream - viz: the \"TIP\" sound of the branch against HCe's window as he sleeps K198 then \"the secret stolen, through the angels, in one's hands\" refers to the meta‐ abstraction + it refers back to \"Ubik\" but from there we go to Lem's analysis, there we end. \"Perturbation in the t reality field\" could imply: what you take to be \"reality\" is a socondary or epiphenomenal realm; there is an outside to it (my surd) able to impinge on it. How something could exist outside of reality, known only by the \"tug\" it exerts on really is hard to explain unless you happen to notice that in Lem's paradigmatic situation this notion is another way of expressing his \"uncanny one-way intrusions that don't belong.\" I say, \"the meta-abstraction was If a meta-abstraction but a simple not realization that Y, which I knew already in theory but did not know it was true, did not know it applied to me + to my reality, + that is is \"Ubik, what, then, is \"Ubik\" in This context? Form axes? The past somehow present? No. \"Ubik\" is true signifies more (although it may include that); to say \"Ubik is the case\" is to say (or to realize / meta abstract) that \"our world is spurious + being fed to us + I know this because I just not caught sight of something that - in Lem's words - does not belong + hence uncannily intrudes from outside + awakens the dreamer to his true situation, or awakens him per see or tells him but still doesn't waken him in any case the statement \"Ubik I tru K199 signifies more or other than Platonic form. axes + the like; it signifies the veridical applicability of the paradigm that Lem extrapolated from \"Ubik\" wherein (the paradism) the \"accidents\" + harticulars are dropped out + the essential situation is \"Ubik\" is related to an overview seen that (as has been noted) I express in novel after novel + story after story, as if I am intuiting something having to do with the spuriousness of reality, a sense of acosmism but \"Ubik\" is to a degree unique in that they are dead + are (really) in the after life; which brings us back to Dante + the Commedia. to the \"ontological evolutionary axis\" by + which one moves from world to world due (apparently) to spiritual growth the Golden Fish sign \"didn't belong,\" If how much more true this is of the in-rush of the world of Acts AD 70 in toto, a month later, the world of which that Golden Fish sign I confirmation of was the tip of the iceberg the meta-abstraction; Acts is the case. Does This mean that \"the uncanny one-way intrusion from outside that don't belong\" are the world of Acts? That would render AD 70 the \"outside\" or true reality + not just another spatio temporal coaxial set. + it would make me dreaming self; Thomas is",
